# Component Structure and Organization

This rule defines how to structure and organize React components in the project.

## 1. Export Pattern

- No default exports in components - always use named exports
- Define each component as `export const [ComponentName]: React.FC<Props>` or `export const [ComponentName]: React.FC` if no props
- Use arrow function body style (implicit return) when the component only returns JSX: `() => ( ... )` instead of `() => { return ... }`

## 2. File and Folder Organization

### Naming Conventions
- **Folder names:** `kebab-case` (e.g., `card-content`, `button-group`, `modal-header`)
- **File names:** `PascalCase` (e.g., `CardContent.tsx`, `ButtonGroup.tsx`, `ModalHeader.tsx`)
- **Component exports:** Match file name (e.g., `CardContent.tsx` exports `CardContent`)

### Structure Rules
- Each component has its own folder
- Each file should have 1 component
- If splitting a component into smaller sub-components, create a `components` folder inside the parent component's folder

## 3. Directory Structure

### Component Directories

- `src/components/common` - shared components between pages
- `src/components/[component-name]` - main component folder (kebab-case)
  - `[ComponentName].tsx` - main component file (PascalCase)
  - `components/` - sub-components folder (if component has sub-components)
    - `[sub-component-name]/` - sub-component folder (kebab-case)
      - `[SubComponentName].tsx` - sub-component file (PascalCase)
    - `[another-sub-component-name]/` - another sub-component folder
      - `[AnotherSubComponentName].tsx` - another sub-component file

### Page Directories

**With internationalization:**
- `src/app/[locale]/[route-name]/page.tsx` → exports `[RouteNamePage]`

**Without internationalization:**
- `src/app/[route-name]/page.tsx` → exports `[RouteNamePage]`


## 4. Props Definition

- Use `type Props` to define component props
- Order props in the following sequence:
  1. Required props first
  2. Optional props next
  3. Function props last

## 5. Examples

### Props Definition

```typescript
type Props = {
  requiredName: string;
  requiredId: number;
  optionalDescription?: string;
  optionalClassName?: string;
  onClick: () => void;
  onSubmit?: (data: DataType) => void;
};
```

### Component with Props

```typescript
type Props = {
  title: string;
  className?: string;
  onClick: () => void;
};

export const Button: React.FC<Props> = ({ title, className, onClick }) => (
  <button className={className} onClick={onClick}>
    {title}
  </button>
);
```

### Component without Props

```typescript
export const Logo: React.FC = () => (
  <div className="logo">
    <img src="/logo.svg" alt="Logo" />
  </div>
);
```
